'''負壓'''是医院和医疗中心用来阻止不同病房之间交叉感染的一种隔离技术<ref name="camil">[http://www.filterair.info/articles/article.cfm/ArticleID/BC9AA829-30F8-4406-8FEE4A1E17574D6B/Page/1 Negative Room Pressure to Prevent Cross-Contamination], Clean Air Solutions, Camil Farr, {{Wayback|url=http://www.filterair.info/articles/article.cfm/ArticleID/BC9AA829-30F8-4406-8FEE4A1E17574D6B/Page/1 |date=20160310214345 }}Retrieved 2010-03-10.</ref><ref>[http://www.engr.psu.edu/AE/iec/abe/control/isolation.asp Isolation Rooms & Pressurization Control] {{Wayback|url=http://www.engr.psu.edu/AE/iec/abe/control/isolation.asp |date=20100304130200 }}, Penn State Department of Architectural Engineering, © 2008 The Pennsylvania State University. Retrieved 2010-03-10.{{Dead link|date=March 2020}}</ref>。負壓需要一種能使病房對外施加的压力低于周围环境對病房的压力的[[通風|排风装置]]，帶有負壓效果的病房稱為'''負壓病房'''。空气在流入負壓病房後，不会从負壓病房中逸出，因为空气会自然地从压力较高的区域流向压力较低的区域，因此負壓病房能阻止含有病菌的空气从病房中逸出<ref>[http://www.airmontinc.com/negative-pressure.php Negative Pressure Isolation Rooms & Tuberculosis (TB) Isolation Rooms], AirMont Inc. Retrieved 2010-03-10. {{Wayback|url=http://www.airmontinc.com/negative-pressure.php |date=20140117043524 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=A practical lesson in negative-pressure isolation ventilation|last=Hoffman|first=P. N.|last2=Weinbren|first2=M. J.|journal=The Journal of Hospital Infection|issue=4|doi=10.1016/j.jhin.2004.04.013|year=2004|volume=57|pages=345–6|pmid=15262397|last3=Stuart|first3=S. A.}}</ref>。

